Colombian Stocks: Bancolombia, Sura, Cementos Argos, Enka

-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 
2011-05-13T21:40:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-13/colombian-stocks-bancolombia-sura-cementos-argos-enka.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index fell 0.1 percent to 14,262.56, while the
Colcap Index rose 0.2 percent to 1,706.76.  Bancolombia SA (BCOLO)  , the nation’s biggest lender,
dropped 1 percent to 28,500 pesos, after topping the list of
Colombian banks that charge the highest ATM fees, El Universal
reported today, citing the country’s financial regulator.  Grupo de Inversiones Suramericana SA (GRUPOSUR)  ,
Bancolombia’s parent company, climbed 2.4 percent to 38,600
pesos, the most since March 18. Bancolombia gained 6.4 percent
in the four days through May 11.  “Bancolombia’s important valuation hadn’t been reflected
in Grupo Sura’s stock until now,” said Mauricio Hernandez,
analyst at Corredores Asociados SA.  Cementos Argos (CEMARGOS CB),  Colombia ’s biggest cement
maker, rose 1.7 percent to 11,000 pesos after buying assets
yesterday with an enterprise value of $760 million from Lafarge
SA, the world’s biggest cement producer.  Textile makers rose after U.S. Trade Representative Ron
Kirk told a House committee yesterday that a pending trade
agreement would expand U.S. exports to Colombia by more than $1
billion. Kirk said the accord will benefit U.S. farmers by
eliminating tariffs on half of current farm exports to Colombia,
according to a statement on the USTR website.  Enka de Colombia SA (ENKA)  , a Medellin-based synthetic
fibers producer, rose 0.7 percent to 13.7 pesos, headed for its
highest close in a month.  Textiles Fabricato SA (FABRI CB), Colombia’s biggest
textile maker, rose 1 percent to 52.5 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
